WEBVTT

00:06.139 --> 00:08.141
<i>PREVIOUSLY ON "WEEDS"...</i>

00:08.175 --> 00:09.910
ANDY: I love her.
But I ran.

00:09.943 --> 00:11.378
AAH!

00:12.145 --> 00:14.047
IT'S OVER.
AUDRA, DON'T.

00:14.081 --> 00:15.048
HE'S A GOOD GUY.

00:15.082 --> 00:16.416
HEY, THOSE ARE MINE!

00:16.450 --> 00:17.985
THEY'RE MINE NOW.

00:18.018 --> 00:20.587
THE NEWMANS WILL SUCCEED
WHERE THE BOTWINS FAILED.

00:20.621 --> 00:21.755
THEY WILL FIND JOBS.

00:21.788 --> 00:23.257
THEY WILL LIVE
A NORMAL LIFE.

00:23.290 --> 00:24.992
YOU'RE LOOKING AT
THE NEW SOUS‐CHEF.

00:25.025 --> 00:26.493
I'D LIKE YOU
TO READ TO ME.

00:27.861 --> 00:29.596
I NEED TO FIND A GIRL
TO HAVE SEX WITH.

00:29.630 --> 00:30.731
[ Laughing ] WHAT?

00:30.764 --> 00:32.065
I LOVE COLLEGE SO MUCH.

00:32.099 --> 00:33.400
I'MIN CHARGE OF AVI.

00:33.433 --> 00:35.068
YOU GUYS
ARE A BAD INFLUENCE.

00:35.102 --> 00:38.372
WE KNOW AVI'S MOTHER
WASN'T KILLED IN THE IRAQ.

00:38.405 --> 00:39.473
TELL US THE TRUTH

00:39.506 --> 00:41.208
OR WE CAN CALL CHILD
PROTECTIVE SERVICES TOGETHER.

00:41.241 --> 00:43.410
YOU HAVE TO KEEP ME ALIVE
SO I CAN LEAD YOU TO HIM.

00:43.443 --> 00:45.546
I DIDN'T KNOW WHAT TO SAY.
I DIDN'T WANT TO DIE.

00:45.579 --> 00:48.815
GUESTS HAVE BEEN ASKING
WHERE THEY CAN GET
CERTAIN HERBAL ITEMS.

00:48.849 --> 00:50.551
WHAT THE HELL IS THIS?
HASH.

00:50.584 --> 00:53.353
WHEN I GET A REQUEST,
I PUT YOU ON THE HOUSEKEEPING
SCHEDULE FOR THOSE ROOMS.

00:53.387 --> 00:54.988
THE GUESTS WILL PUT THE MONEY
UNDER THE PILLOW,

00:55.022 --> 00:55.989
YOU LEAVE THE HASH.

00:56.023 --> 00:57.691
YOU GOT CASH?

00:57.724 --> 00:59.393
Nancy: SO, YOUR TRIMMINGS,
YOU JUST THROW THEM AWAY?

00:59.426 --> 01:00.194
I'LL TAKE 'EM.

01:00.227 --> 01:02.863
I'M THINKING $100 BUYS ME A LOT.

01:02.896 --> 01:04.364
I GET SHIT <i>DONE.</i>

01:04.398 --> 01:06.166
Cop: YOU!

01:06.200 --> 01:07.434
DON'T FUCKIN' MOVE!

01:19.413 --> 01:20.480
Run.

01:20.514 --> 01:21.949
YOU TWO ARE IN DEEP SHIT.

01:21.982 --> 01:23.283
TALK TO ME ABOUT THE VAN.

01:23.317 --> 01:24.484
Run now.

01:24.518 --> 01:25.652
Run fast.

01:25.686 --> 01:27.321
WHAT?

01:27.354 --> 01:29.189
I ‐‐ VAN.

01:29.223 --> 01:30.624
YES, YOUR VAN
THAT WE JUST BOOTED.

01:30.657 --> 01:34.027
THE VAN THAT HAS OVER $6,000
IN UNPAID PARKING TICKETS.

01:34.061 --> 01:36.129
THE VAN WHOSE PLATES
DON'T MATCH THE VEHICLE.

01:36.163 --> 01:37.598
RING A FUCKIN' BELL?

01:37.631 --> 01:39.399
THAT SUBURBAN MINIVAN?

01:39.433 --> 01:41.101
NO. EW.

01:41.134 --> 01:43.337
YEAH, EW.
TOTALLY.

01:43.370 --> 01:44.404
BULLSHIT.

01:44.438 --> 01:46.073
NEIGHBORS SAW A WHITE COUPLE
FITTING YOUR DESCRIPTION

01:46.106 --> 01:47.441
GET OUT OF IT AN HOUR AGO.

01:47.474 --> 01:50.310
WE'RE COOL PEOPLE.

01:50.344 --> 01:51.645
URBANITES.

01:51.678 --> 01:53.080
IT'S SORT OF OUR IDENTITY.

01:53.113 --> 01:56.049
IT'S SILLY, WE KNOW,
THESE DAYS.

01:56.083 --> 01:58.519
WHEN GONORRHEA
IS BECOMING DRUG‐RESISTANT.

01:58.552 --> 02:01.021
WHEN IRAN IS TEETERING.

02:01.054 --> 02:02.189
TURDUCKEN.

02:02.222 --> 02:03.624
THE HELL
ARE YOU BABBLING ABOUT?

02:03.657 --> 02:04.491
THAT'S NOT YOUR VAN?

02:04.525 --> 02:07.127
THOSE ARE JUST A STATEMENT
OF DEFEAT.

02:07.160 --> 02:10.464
LIKE, "I'M JUST GONNA BUY INTO
THE WHOLE THING."

02:10.497 --> 02:11.498
DEFEAT?

02:11.532 --> 02:14.668
OR MAYBE YOU'RE TRYING
TO IMPRESS SOMEONE

02:14.701 --> 02:16.570
BY BEING SOMETHING YOU'RE NOT,
WHEN, IN TRUTH,

02:16.603 --> 02:18.705
YOU DON'T LOVE THIS PERSON
AND YOU NEVER REALLY DID

02:18.739 --> 02:22.643
AND MAYBE THEY'RE JUST REALLY
JUDGY WITH WEIRD LIMP HAIR...

02:22.676 --> 02:23.644
FOR EXAMPLE.

02:23.677 --> 02:25.212
Cop: WHERE'S YOUR
VEHICLE, THEN?

02:25.245 --> 02:26.947
OR ARE YOU JUST OUT
FOR A STROLL?

02:26.980 --> 02:27.948
JUST TAKING OUT THE...

02:27.981 --> 02:29.116
LAWN TRIMMINGS.

02:29.149 --> 02:30.117
WE SHOULD DO THAT.

02:30.150 --> 02:31.818
HONEY, WHERE'D YOU PUT
THE BINS?

02:31.852 --> 02:33.987
BINS?
I FOUND BINS.

02:34.021 --> 02:37.424
[ CHUCKLES ] YAY, BINS!

02:40.727 --> 02:43.497
Back of the house, back of
the house, back of the house.

02:43.530 --> 02:46.099
Cop: WAIT!

02:46.133 --> 02:47.267
BLUE IS RECYCLING.

02:47.301 --> 02:49.269
YOU SAID THOSE
WERE LAWN TRIMMINGS.

02:49.303 --> 02:51.572
[ LAUGHS ]

02:51.605 --> 02:54.508
DAMN THIS COLORBLINDNESS.
IT'S A TRUE STORY.

02:54.541 --> 02:56.243
WE SUPPORT YOU

02:56.276 --> 03:00.180
IN YOUR CURRENT FUNDING FIGHT
WITH THE CITY.

03:00.214 --> 03:03.450
SOMETIMES WE USE
THE BACK DOOR.

03:08.422 --> 03:10.657
I BET SHE WASN'T EVEN
IN THE ARMY.

03:10.691 --> 03:12.893
YOU REALLY THINK
THE MILITARY‐INDUSTRIAL COMPLEX

03:12.926 --> 03:14.127
WOULD LET
THE REAL STORY GET OUT?

03:14.161 --> 03:16.096
I'M CALLING
CHILD PROTECTIVE SERVICES.

03:16.129 --> 03:17.397
CHERYL, PHONE.
GREAT.

03:17.431 --> 03:18.999
AND MAYBE
I'LL TELL THEM ABOUT

03:19.032 --> 03:20.868
ALLISON'S LITTLE
PRESCRIPTION FRIENDS.

03:20.901 --> 03:22.936
NOT SUPPOSED TO BE DRIVING
WITH A CHILD

03:22.970 --> 03:24.438
IN THE VEHICLE ON THOSE,
ARE YOU, ALLY?

03:24.471 --> 03:27.140
AND, CHERYL, I'M NOT SURE
HOW THEY'D FEEL ABOUT A WOMAN

03:27.174 --> 03:29.576
WHO STILL LETS HER 5‐YEAR‐OLD
BREAST‐FEED.

03:29.610 --> 03:31.278
CHERYL.

03:31.311 --> 03:34.114
AND, REBEKAH,
YOU DON'T NEED ANYONE

03:34.147 --> 03:37.184
LOOKING INTO THE VISA STATUS
OF YOUR HOUSEKEEPER, DO YOU?

03:37.217 --> 03:40.654
WHAT IS SHE, HONDURAN?
GUATEMALAN?

03:40.687 --> 03:43.190
DON'T FUCK WITH ME, BITCHES.

03:46.793 --> 03:48.262
WHY DID THIS HAPPEN?

03:48.295 --> 03:51.131
PAYBACK, NANCE.
IT'S THE KARMIC BOOMERANG.

03:51.164 --> 03:54.168
OF COURSE
THE PLATES SILAS AND I STOLE

03:54.201 --> 03:56.703
WOULD BE
FROM A FELON‐LEVEL SCOFFLAW.

03:56.737 --> 03:58.739
KARMA BOOMERANGED.

03:58.772 --> 03:59.740
WHERE WAS I?

03:59.773 --> 04:01.742
OH, YEAH.
NOT WHERE ‐‐ WHO.

04:01.775 --> 04:02.809
YOU'RE NANCY BOTWIN,

04:02.843 --> 04:04.845
AND SINCE IT DIDN'T
DIRECTLY AFFECT YOU,

04:04.878 --> 04:06.280
YOU DIDN'T FUCKING NOTICE.

04:06.313 --> 04:08.282
MAN,
THESE THINGS ARE WELL‐MADE.

04:08.315 --> 04:10.384
WHAT ARE THEY, CHINESE?
EXCUSE ME.

04:11.718 --> 04:12.886
WHY ARE YOU MAD AT ME?

04:12.920 --> 04:14.688
[ SIGHS ]

04:14.721 --> 04:15.756
"JUDGY"?

04:15.789 --> 04:17.491
OH, THAT.

04:19.193 --> 04:21.228
"WEIRD HAIR"?
"LIMP HAIR"?

04:21.261 --> 04:23.263
SHE HAPPENS TO HAVE
VERY LUSTROUS HAIR.

04:23.297 --> 04:25.132
I‐I DON'T HAVE ANY IDEA
WHERE THAT CAME FROM.

04:25.165 --> 04:27.968
I SUPPOSE I HAD THOUGHTS. THEY
CHOSE THAT MOMENT TO COME OUT.

04:28.001 --> 04:29.937
NOT THOUGHTS.
YOU HAD FEELINGS.

04:29.970 --> 04:32.673
YOUR REAL FEELINGS,
WHICH YOU HOARDED LIKE A ‐‐

04:32.706 --> 04:36.009
LIKE A CHIPMUNK
IN YOUR CHEEKS.

04:36.043 --> 04:37.311
ARE YOU SURE
THAT'S A GOOD IDEA?

04:37.344 --> 04:40.280
"EVERYTHING'S FINE," YOU SAID.
"MAZEL TOV," YOU SAID.

04:40.314 --> 04:42.616
BUT YOUR CHEEKS WERE BULGING,
AND I COULD SEE IT,

04:42.649 --> 04:44.518
AND AUDRA COULD SEE IT,
AND IT DROVE A WEDGE.

04:44.551 --> 04:46.420
YOU RAN OUT ON <i>HER.</i>

04:46.453 --> 04:47.254
[ GRUNTS ]

04:47.287 --> 04:49.489
GIRLS KNOW THESE THINGS,
NANCE.

04:49.523 --> 04:51.458
'CAUSE THEY'RE MORE IN TUNE
WITH THE SUBTLETIES

04:51.491 --> 04:54.261
OF INTERPERSONAL,
KISSY STUFF FLYING AROUND.

04:54.294 --> 04:56.230
AND ALSO BECAUSE,
IN THE END,

04:56.263 --> 04:59.733
YOU'RE ALL PETTY, JEALOUS,
DADDY‐ISSUE EVERYTHING‐RUINERS.

04:59.766 --> 05:01.068
YEAH,
IT'S STARTING TO SMOKE.

05:01.101 --> 05:04.071
YOU'RE LIKE THE DOG ON THE
BRIDGE THAT WANTS BOTH BONES.

05:04.104 --> 05:05.906
THAT'S YOU.
YOU WANT ALL THE BONES.

05:05.939 --> 05:08.275
I DON'T KNOW WHY YOU'RE HEAPING
THIS SHIT ON ME RIGHT NOW.
YEAH, YEAH, YEAH.

05:08.308 --> 05:10.077
BUT I REALLY THINK YOU SHOULD
FOCUS AWAY FROM THINGS...
YOU KNOW EXACTLY WHY,
AND HERE WE GO AGAIN

05:10.110 --> 05:11.645
TALKING OVER EACH OTHER.
...LIKE DOGS AND BONES.

05:11.678 --> 05:13.413
IT'S REALLY GETTING OLD,
NANCE.

05:13.447 --> 05:15.215
GEEZ, GOD!

05:15.916 --> 05:17.251
BOOMERANG.

05:17.284 --> 05:19.887
DAMN IT!

05:19.920 --> 05:21.355
[ SIGHS ]

05:21.388 --> 05:22.823
WHAT NOW?

05:22.856 --> 05:25.125
THE VAN'S NO GOOD FOR US
ANYMORE, ANYWAY.

05:25.158 --> 05:27.394
SOON, THE VIN'S GONNA HIT
THE RIGHT DATABASE,

05:27.427 --> 05:30.063
AND WE'RE LIVIN'
IN FUCKED CITY, U. S. A.

05:30.097 --> 05:31.765
EVERYONE'S GONNA BE LOOKING
FOR US HERE.

05:31.798 --> 05:33.634
I THOUGHT YOU REGISTERED THE VAN
UNDER A DIFFERENT NAME.

05:33.667 --> 05:35.569
YEAH ‐‐ SHANE BOTWIN.

05:36.703 --> 05:39.606
'CAUSE IT WAS THE ONLY OTHER
SOCIAL THAT I KNEW BY HEART.

05:39.640 --> 05:40.807
HOW DO YOU KNOW SHA‐‐

05:40.841 --> 05:42.442
NEVER MIND.

05:42.476 --> 05:44.011
GOODBYE, SEATTLE.

05:44.044 --> 05:46.146
[ LAUGHS ]

05:46.180 --> 05:48.048
IT NEVER EVEN RAINED.

05:48.081 --> 05:50.484
WHAT A RIP‐OFF.

05:55.422 --> 05:56.757
[ ALARM CHIRPS ]

05:56.790 --> 05:58.825
WOMAN:
Mr. Botwin, our sensors indicate

05:58.859 --> 06:02.396
that you've experienced
a sudden loss of tire pressure.

06:02.429 --> 06:03.397
Hello?

06:03.430 --> 06:05.165
Mr. Botwin?

06:05.199 --> 06:06.200
Hello?

06:06.233 --> 06:09.770
WHY DIDN'T ANYBODY TELL ME
HOW AWESOME COLLEGE IS?

06:09.803 --> 06:11.438
'CAUSE YOU WERE NEVER
GONNA GO.

06:11.471 --> 06:12.573
IT WOULD JUST BE MEAN,

06:12.606 --> 06:14.441
LIKE TELLING A BLIND PERSON
HOW AWESOME COLORS ARE.

06:14.474 --> 06:15.375
SHUT UP.

06:15.409 --> 06:18.078
I MAY NOT BE ACADEMIC SMART,
BUT I'M SMART.

06:18.111 --> 06:20.814
I STARTED MY OWN BUSINESS.
I READ.

06:20.848 --> 06:22.149
TO OLD DUDES
IN YOUR UNDERWEAR.

06:22.182 --> 06:23.550
THAT'S IT.
YOU'RE GOING DOWN.

06:23.584 --> 06:24.985
THAT WHAT THE OLD MAN SAID?

06:26.420 --> 06:27.321
CATLIKE REFLEXES.

06:27.354 --> 06:29.523
PERFECT, CONSIDERING
YOU'RE A TOTAL PUSSY.

06:29.556 --> 06:32.092
TELL THAT TO PILAR.

06:32.125 --> 06:35.229
WHO'S THE BLOND?
IS THAT HIS BROTHER?

06:35.262 --> 06:36.430
PLEASE.
THEY LOOK NOTHING ALIKE.

06:36.463 --> 06:38.498
I BET THEY'RE DOING IT
WITH EACH OTHER.

06:39.933 --> 06:41.869
WELL, WHATEVER THEIR
RELATIONSHIP IS,

06:41.902 --> 06:44.171
THEY ARE CLEARLY NOT EQUIPPED
TO RAISE A BABY.

06:44.204 --> 06:47.374
OH, MY GOD, THEY JUST SPILLED
CROUTONS ON HIS BLANKIE.

06:47.407 --> 06:49.710
WHAT IF HE'S
GLUTEN‐INTOLERANT?

06:49.743 --> 06:50.944
WHAT'S GLUTEN?

06:50.978 --> 06:52.646
[ SIGHS ]
SHUT UP, CHERYL.

06:52.679 --> 06:55.549
NO BREAD!

06:55.582 --> 06:56.416
I WAS GETTING INTO TROUBLE

06:56.450 --> 06:58.118
WHILE YOU WERE STILL
WETTING THE BED.

06:58.151 --> 06:59.286
YEAH,
STEALING VIDEO CAMERAS

06:59.319 --> 07:01.388
AND KNOCKING UP
YOUR DEAF GIRLFRIEND.

07:01.421 --> 07:02.456
GANGSTER.

07:02.489 --> 07:05.392
FACE IT, SILAS, WE'RE HARD CORE
AND YOU'RE PG‐13.

07:05.425 --> 07:06.793
WHAT'S YOUR POINT?

07:06.827 --> 07:08.295
YOU'RE THE BLOND SHEEP
OF THIS FAMILY.

07:08.328 --> 07:09.563
I THINK YOU WERE ADOPTED.

07:09.596 --> 07:11.632
[ CHUCKLES ] I WISH.

07:11.665 --> 07:14.334
THAT WOULD BE AWESOME.

07:14.368 --> 07:16.703
CHECK, PLEASE?

07:16.737 --> 07:18.105
YOU GOING TO WORK?

07:18.138 --> 07:20.574
FUCK THE HOTEL.

07:20.607 --> 07:23.010
I'M GOING BACK TO SCHOOL.

07:24.811 --> 07:27.314
[ BREATHING HEAVILY ]

07:29.149 --> 07:31.185
OH, MY GOD,
IN ALL HIS GLORY.

07:31.218 --> 07:33.420
I HAVE NOT BEEN
A FAITHFUL SERVANT.

07:33.453 --> 07:36.223
IN FACT, I'VE BEEN
A PRETTY MISERABLE SERVANT.

07:36.256 --> 07:37.324
YOU'RE HURTING THE TREE.

07:37.357 --> 07:39.927
I TRIED TO READ THE BIBLE.
I DID.

07:39.960 --> 07:43.330
BUT IT ALWAYS FELT LIKE
A MUCH LESS AWESOME
"LORD OF THE RINGS."

07:43.363 --> 07:44.731
WHAT ARE YOU WRITING,
ANYWAY?

07:44.765 --> 07:45.933
MY AND MARIA'S INITIALS.

07:45.966 --> 07:48.001
I CARVED OUR NAMES
ON OUR FIRST DATE.

07:48.035 --> 07:50.103
AND I DO IT STILL.

07:50.137 --> 07:52.072
WOMEN APPRECIATE
THE LITTLE THINGS.

07:52.105 --> 07:54.007
I WOULD LIKE TO BELIEVE
THE WHOLE THING ‐‐

07:54.041 --> 07:56.143
KARMA, AN AFTERLIFE.

07:56.176 --> 07:58.011
I WOULD LIKE TO GO TO HEAVEN,

07:58.045 --> 08:00.581
HAVE DRINKS WITH COOL PEOPLE
I NEVER GOT TO MEET ‐‐

08:00.614 --> 08:05.452
MOM, JAMES DEAN, HARRIET TUBMAN,
DAD, PATRICK SWAYZE.

08:05.485 --> 08:07.287
I CAN'T DIE LIKE THIS.

08:07.321 --> 08:10.157
I ALWAYS WANTED TO BE BURIED
WITH MY BANJO AND SNACKS

08:10.190 --> 08:12.993
AND HEARTBROKEN WOMEN AND DOGS
THROWING THEMSELVES ON MY GRAVE.

08:13.026 --> 08:15.896
I ONCE LOVED A GIRL
FROM THE NEIGHBORHOOD

08:15.929 --> 08:18.432
NAMED ROSA GALINDO.

08:18.465 --> 08:19.900
MM.

08:19.933 --> 08:21.602
I CARVED HER NAME, TOO.

08:22.936 --> 08:24.972
INTO
MANUEL GONZALEZ'S THIGH.

08:25.005 --> 08:27.474
OH, GOD,
PLEASE HEAR MY PRAYERS.

08:27.508 --> 08:28.775
LET'S KILL HIM NOW.

08:28.809 --> 08:30.410
IF WE LEAVE SOON,
I CAN BE HOME

08:30.444 --> 08:32.145
FOR JULIA'S TAP RECITAL
TOMORROW.

08:32.179 --> 08:34.147
I NEED A MIRACLE.
I NEED A MIRACLE!

08:34.181 --> 08:36.149
YOU'RE WASTING
YOUR FINAL MOMENTS.

08:36.183 --> 08:38.151
I'M NOT SUPPOSED TO DIE HERE.
I KNOW IT.

08:38.185 --> 08:40.854
STEP IN, GUY.
SAVE ME, COME ON.

08:40.888 --> 08:42.523
GOD HAS BETTER THINGS
TO WORRY ABOUT

08:42.556 --> 08:43.957
THAN ASSHOLES LIKE YOU.

08:43.991 --> 08:46.159
THIS SUCKS SO MUCH.

08:46.193 --> 08:48.462
[ CELLPHONE RINGS ]

08:50.364 --> 08:52.232
HELLO?

08:52.266 --> 08:53.667
WHAT?

08:53.700 --> 08:55.869
YES, THIS IS SHANE BOTWIN.

08:55.903 --> 08:58.272
THE TIRE?

08:58.305 --> 09:00.073
YES.

09:00.107 --> 09:01.742
REMIND ME WHERE I LEFT IT.

09:07.080 --> 09:08.482
THEY FOUND THE VAN.

09:08.515 --> 09:11.485
HOLY SHIT.

09:11.518 --> 09:12.920
THAT'S SO SPOOKY.

09:12.953 --> 09:15.389
UH,
ARE WE STILL GONNA KILL HIM?

09:15.422 --> 09:17.958
NO!

09:17.991 --> 09:19.893
I THINK GOD
WANTS HIM ALIVE.

09:19.927 --> 09:21.595
Thank you.

09:21.628 --> 09:22.930
Thank you.
Thank you.

09:22.963 --> 09:24.398
VAMOS, CABRóN. VAMOS.

09:24.431 --> 09:26.500
OKAY, OKAY.

09:40.480 --> 09:43.217
WHERE'S MINE?

09:43.250 --> 09:45.252
YOU SAID
YOU DIDN'T WANT ANYTHING.

09:45.285 --> 09:47.087
YOU COULD HAVE
GOT ME SOMETHING ‐‐

09:47.120 --> 09:48.755
A FISH SANDWICH
OF CONTRITION.

09:48.789 --> 09:50.557
PENANCE FRIES.

09:50.591 --> 09:54.661
AN "I'M SORRY I RUINED
YOUR NEW CAREER" McMUFFIN.

09:56.129 --> 09:57.231
LET'S FACE IT, ANDY.

09:57.264 --> 09:59.433
YOU WOULD HAVE SCREWED IT UP
WITHIN A WEEK.

09:59.466 --> 10:00.400
WHAT?

10:02.002 --> 10:05.472
YOU DON'T ACTUALLY WANT
WHAT YOU CAN HAVE.

10:05.506 --> 10:07.541
THAT'S WHY YOU WANT ME.

10:07.574 --> 10:10.377
'CAUSE YOU CAN'T HAVE ME.

10:15.449 --> 10:17.017
[ SLURPS ]

10:17.050 --> 10:18.118
NONE OF YOU GIVE A SHIT.

10:18.151 --> 10:20.187
NOT REALLY.
AND I GET IT.

10:20.220 --> 10:21.555
WHY LEARN ABOUT THE WORLD

10:21.588 --> 10:24.625
WHEN WITHIN SEVEN SECONDS
OF OPENING YOUR MacBook,

10:24.658 --> 10:28.262
YOU COULD BE IN
A PHOTO‐REALISTIC GRENADE BATTLE

10:28.295 --> 10:30.197
WITH AN 8‐YEAR‐OLD IN SAGINAW

10:30.230 --> 10:33.934
OR WATCHING UNDERAGED
HUNGARIAN GANGBANG VIDEOS?

10:33.967 --> 10:35.502
BUT LET'S MAKE A DEAL.

10:35.536 --> 10:39.373
ONE HOUR TWICE A WEEK,
WE'RE GONNA BE ENGAGED.

10:39.406 --> 10:40.607
FIGHT ME.

10:40.641 --> 10:44.044
CALL ME A LIBERAL, ELITIST,
LATTE‐SIPPING SOCIALIST SCUMBAG.

10:44.077 --> 10:46.013
JUST CARE ABOUT SOMETHING.

10:46.046 --> 10:48.081
'CAUSE WHEN YOU'RE DONE
WHATEVERING YOUR LIFE AWAY,

10:48.115 --> 10:50.684
THE WORLD WILL ABSOLUTELY
BLOW YOUR FUCKING MINDS.

10:50.717 --> 10:52.853
HE IS SO RIGHT.

10:52.886 --> 10:56.390
LET'S BEGIN.

10:58.325 --> 11:02.729
YOU AND I ‐‐
WE'LL NEVER, RIGHT?

11:02.763 --> 11:04.765
JUST SAY WE'LL NEVER.

11:07.234 --> 11:10.170
THEY ALL DIE, ANDY.

11:10.204 --> 11:12.573
I LIKE YOU TOO MUCH
TO WANT YOU TO DIE.

11:12.606 --> 11:16.276
HOLY COW, YOU'RE RIGHT.
THEY DO ALL DIE.

11:16.310 --> 11:17.711
[ SLURPS ]

11:17.744 --> 11:19.279
YOUR PUSSY'S
A DEATH SENTENCE.

11:20.480 --> 11:22.616
A PENIS FLYTRAP.

11:24.117 --> 11:25.819
YOU'RE DR. KAVAGIAN.

11:25.853 --> 11:27.254
ALL RIGHT, THEN.

11:27.287 --> 11:30.257
WAIT.
ESTEBAN'S NOT DEAD.

11:30.290 --> 11:32.726
NOT YET.

11:32.759 --> 11:34.261
[ SLURPS ]

11:39.600 --> 11:44.805
SO, BY NOT LOVING ME,
YOU'RE ACTUALLY SAVING ME?

11:44.838 --> 11:48.542
BY NOT SLEEPING WITH YOU,
I'M PROBABLY SAVING YOU, YEAH.

11:55.816 --> 11:58.318
[ SLURPING ]

11:58.352 --> 12:00.854
[ SIGHS ]

12:00.888 --> 12:02.789
YOU HAVE TO RELEASE ME,
NANCE.

12:02.823 --> 12:04.157
THIS IS THE MOMENT
RIGHT NOW,

12:04.191 --> 12:07.661
WAITING FOR
THE NUMBER 43 BUS.

12:07.694 --> 12:09.096
LET ME GO.
RELEASE ME.

12:09.129 --> 12:13.066
SAY, "IT'LL NEVER HAPPEN."

12:14.468 --> 12:15.435
COME ON. DO IT!

12:15.469 --> 12:16.436
I CAN'T.

12:16.470 --> 12:17.671
WHY NOT?

12:17.704 --> 12:18.772
I'M AFRAID.

12:18.805 --> 12:20.240
OF WHAT?
YOU KNOW.

12:20.274 --> 12:23.410
NO, I DON'T.
THAT YOU'LL LEAVE ME.

12:24.678 --> 12:26.446
US.

12:28.949 --> 12:30.217
WAIT.

12:30.250 --> 12:35.389
SO REALLY, THEN...
I HAVE ALL THE POWER HERE.

12:35.422 --> 12:36.490
NOT YOU.

12:38.425 --> 12:41.495
I SU‐‐
I SUPPOSE YOU DO, YEAH.

12:41.528 --> 12:44.431
YEAH.

12:44.464 --> 12:46.567
I HAVE THE POWER.

12:50.470 --> 12:52.105
I HAVE THE POWER.

12:52.139 --> 12:55.409
THAT SAID, YOU NEVER KNOW WHAT
COULD HAPPEN IN THE FUTURE.

12:55.442 --> 12:56.443
[ SLURPS ]

12:58.111 --> 13:01.281
YOU HAVE NO IDEA HOW LONG
I'VE WANTED TO DO THAT.

13:08.388 --> 13:10.357
[ SNIFFLES ]

13:21.802 --> 13:22.870
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

13:22.903 --> 13:25.005
WHAT'S WRONG WITH YOU?

13:25.038 --> 13:26.707
YOUR MOM
WON'T RELEASE ME.

13:26.740 --> 13:28.642
WE HAVE TO LEAVE SEATTLE.

13:28.675 --> 13:30.377
OKAY. WHY?

13:30.410 --> 13:32.546
'CAUSE UNCLE ANDY WAS STARTING
TO FIND HIS OWN THING.

13:32.579 --> 13:34.014
WE CAN'T HAVE THAT!

13:34.047 --> 13:36.283
WE'RE ON THE RUN NOW, HONEY.
IT'S WHAT WE DO.

13:36.316 --> 13:38.719
AND SILAS FUCKED UP
WITH THE LICENSE PLATES.

13:38.752 --> 13:40.354
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]

13:40.387 --> 13:43.023
HUH.

13:49.796 --> 13:51.198
YEAH.

13:51.231 --> 13:54.968
ARE YOU THE GRANDMA?
YOU CUNTS FOLLOWED ME?

13:55.002 --> 13:56.203
Excuse me just one second.

13:56.236 --> 13:58.338
WE DON'T USE THAT WORD.

13:58.372 --> 13:59.373
"GRANDMA"?

13:59.406 --> 14:00.541
NO, "CUNT."

14:00.574 --> 14:01.542
OR "GRANDMA."

14:01.575 --> 14:02.809
WE DON'T USE EITHER.

14:02.843 --> 14:05.145
CAN YOU DEAL WITH
WHATEVER THIS IS?

14:05.179 --> 14:07.481
DON'T FORGET ‐‐
I HAVE THE POWER.

14:07.514 --> 14:08.782
I KNOW YOU DO.

14:08.815 --> 14:10.784
WHERE ARE YOU GOING?

14:10.817 --> 14:14.021
TO GET MONEY AND A CAR
OR TO TAKE A TRAIN

14:14.054 --> 14:17.124
TO SOME QUAINT NEW ENGLAND
SEASIDE VILLAGE

14:17.157 --> 14:19.660
AND LEAVE YOU ALL FOR GOOD.

14:19.693 --> 14:21.094
I HAVEN'T DECIDED WHICH.

14:21.128 --> 14:23.197
I DRINK, TOO, SOMETIMES.

14:23.230 --> 14:25.499
RANDY HERE WILL ANSWER
ALL YOUR QUESTIONS.

14:32.439 --> 14:34.408
HEY,
LOOK WHAT THE CAT DRAGGED IN.

14:34.441 --> 14:36.543
HAVE YOU SEEN DON?
I NEED AN ADVANCE.

14:36.577 --> 14:38.912
YEAH, HAVE YOU MET DON?
THAT'S NOT GONNA HAPPEN.

14:38.946 --> 14:40.147
[ SIGHS ] SHIT.

14:40.180 --> 14:42.049
OH, HERE'S AN IDEA.

14:42.082 --> 14:46.486
IF YOU NEED MONEY,
MAKE YOUR FUCKING DROPS.

14:47.855 --> 14:49.022
YOU GOT MORE STUFF, RIGHT?

14:49.056 --> 14:50.557
OF COURSE.

15:15.482 --> 15:16.583
JOE.

15:16.617 --> 15:18.785
JOE.

15:18.819 --> 15:20.654
PICK UP, GOD DAMN IT!

15:24.858 --> 15:25.926
OH.

15:25.959 --> 15:27.661
THIS IS MY ROOM.

15:27.694 --> 15:29.363
YOU SEE,
I'M ON THE SCHEDULE.

15:42.109 --> 15:44.144
CAN I PLEASE HAVE MY MONEY?

15:47.414 --> 15:49.349
UNBELIEVABLE.

15:49.383 --> 15:50.851
[ CHUCKLES ]

15:50.884 --> 15:53.620
IT'S THE BOOMERANG.

15:53.654 --> 15:55.088
DID JOE TELL YOU?

15:55.122 --> 15:57.291
JOE AIN'T HAVE
TO TELL ME SHIT.

15:57.324 --> 15:59.226
CHANGING THE SCHEDULE
LAST MINUTE?

15:59.259 --> 16:01.094
"NATHALIE HAS TO CLEAN
THIS ROOM.

16:01.128 --> 16:02.563
NATHALIE HAS TO CLEAN
THAT ROOM."

16:02.596 --> 16:04.565
I'M THINKING,
"THIS BITCH MUST BE BAD OFF,

16:04.598 --> 16:07.935
FUCKING A MINI‐HEEB
FOR BETTER SHIFTS."

16:07.968 --> 16:10.204
THEN I DISCOVERED
YOUR LITTLE PACKAGES.

16:10.237 --> 16:12.739
BALLER‐ASS DRUG DEALER.

16:12.773 --> 16:15.275
I'M LEAVING.
I'M DONE.

16:16.276 --> 16:18.178
YOU KNOW THE WORST THING?

16:18.212 --> 16:19.947
NOW I FEEL LIKE AN IDIOT

16:19.980 --> 16:22.883
FOR PLAYING BY THE RULES
THIS WHOLE TIME.

16:22.916 --> 16:26.253
FUCK YOU.

16:26.286 --> 16:30.891
MAKING ME FEEL LIKE A SUCKER
FOR TRYING TO STAY CORRECT.

16:30.924 --> 16:32.960
LOOK, IT'S ALL SET UP.

16:32.993 --> 16:34.728
YOU CAN TAKE OVER.

16:34.761 --> 16:36.463
JUST GIVE ME
TODAY'S MONEY.

16:36.496 --> 16:39.566
I COULD HAVE BOUGHT
ONE OF THESE ANY TIME.

16:41.535 --> 16:42.536
TOBLERONE.

16:42.569 --> 16:45.072
THEY ALWAYS FELT LIKE
SOMETHING SOMEBODY LIKE ME

16:45.105 --> 16:46.573
AIN'T SUPPOSED TO EAT.

16:46.607 --> 16:48.308
"GIRL,
IT'S FOR WHITE PEOPLE.

16:48.342 --> 16:52.045
BETTER GET YOUR BLACK ASS
TO THE STORE AND BUY A KIT KAT."

16:53.680 --> 16:54.982
THE MONEY.

16:55.015 --> 16:56.283
MONEY, PLEASE.

16:56.316 --> 16:58.285
NO.

16:58.318 --> 17:01.288
AND I THINK YOU ABOUT
TO GIVE ME THEM DRUGS, TOO.

17:01.321 --> 17:05.092
THE DRUGS YOU WAS GONNA LEAVE
FOR 812, 315, 1401.

17:05.125 --> 17:07.261
I THINK
THAT'S WHAT HAPPENS NOW.

17:07.294 --> 17:08.695
I'M DRY.
I COULDN'T GET ANY MORE.

17:08.729 --> 17:10.397
SO YOU WAS GONNA
TAKE THE MONEY

17:10.430 --> 17:13.200
AND LEAVE THESE FOOLS
NOTHING?

17:13.233 --> 17:14.968
YOU WORSE THAN I THOUGHT.

17:15.002 --> 17:17.404
FUCK YOU, LATRICE.

17:17.437 --> 17:19.273
REALLY, FUCK YOU!

17:19.306 --> 17:20.874
[ LAUGHS ]

17:20.908 --> 17:22.843
YOU REALLY AIN'T GOOD
AT SHIT.

17:22.876 --> 17:25.646
[ LAUGHS ]

17:34.121 --> 17:37.224
YOU SHOULD HAVE SOMEBODY
CLEAN UP IN 1212.

17:37.257 --> 17:40.661
I LEFT A MESS IN THERE.

17:40.694 --> 17:43.430
COULD YOU TAKE THAT?
THANK YOU.

17:47.134 --> 17:50.237
I HAVE NEVER FELT
AS CONNECTED TO ANYONE

17:50.270 --> 17:52.139
AS I FEEL TO MY BABIES.

17:52.172 --> 17:53.307
THE BOND IS THAT STRONG.

17:53.340 --> 17:55.309
OH, MY GOD!
I LIVE FOR MY BABIES!

17:55.342 --> 17:57.077
MM‐HMM.
BABIES ARE THE BEST.

17:57.110 --> 17:59.146
YOU SHOULD HAVE A BABY.
I WAS GONNA ‐‐

17:59.179 --> 18:01.114
I WAS GONNA HAVE A BABY
WITH A WIFE.

18:01.148 --> 18:03.884
NOW I'M IN SEATTLE
WITH HER, SEXLESS.

18:03.917 --> 18:06.253
SEXLESS IN SEATTLE.

18:06.286 --> 18:08.856
SHE SAYS THAT I HAVE THE POWER,
BUT I DON'T.

18:08.889 --> 18:11.391
I HAVE NO POWER.
I HAVE NO WIFE.

18:11.425 --> 18:13.093
I HAVE NO BOND.

18:13.126 --> 18:17.164
MY HUSBAND DIDN'T LEAVE ME
FOR A 22‐YEAR‐OLD.

18:17.197 --> 18:19.499
HE'S LIVING ALONE
AT THE OAKWOODS.

18:19.533 --> 18:22.870
JUST SAYING THAT HE LEFT ME
FOR A 22‐YEAR‐OLD

18:22.903 --> 18:24.605
IS LESS EMBARRASSING
THAN THE TRUTH ‐‐

18:24.638 --> 18:28.375
THAT HE LEFT ME FOR...
NOT ME.

18:28.408 --> 18:31.411
THAT'S AWFUL.

18:31.445 --> 18:32.212
[ SIGHS ]

18:32.246 --> 18:35.816
NOW I'LL NEVER HAVE
ANOTHER BABY.

18:35.849 --> 18:37.751
YOU CAN HAVE ONE
IF YOU WANT TO.

18:37.784 --> 18:40.420
[ BOTH CHUCKLE ]

18:43.824 --> 18:45.792
ANY CELIAC IN YOUR FAMILY?

18:45.826 --> 18:46.960
WHO?

18:46.994 --> 18:48.128
GALACTOSEMIA?

18:48.161 --> 18:50.097
I DON'T THINK SO.

18:50.130 --> 18:51.899
CYSTIC FIBROSIS?

18:51.932 --> 18:53.267
NEUROFIBROMATOSIS?

18:53.300 --> 18:55.068
MM. THIS IS REALLY WEIRD
DIRTY TALK.

18:55.102 --> 18:56.637
SORRY. WE CAN DO
FAMILY HISTORIES LATER.

18:56.670 --> 18:57.838
PUT A BABY IN ME.

18:57.871 --> 18:58.839
WAIT.

18:58.872 --> 19:00.007
WHAT? NO.

19:00.040 --> 19:01.508
NO, I CAN'T HAVE
A BABY WITH YOU.

19:01.542 --> 19:03.143
COME ON, SHITHEAD.
GIVE ME YOUR SPERM.

19:03.177 --> 19:04.178
IT DOESN'T COST YOU
ANYTHING.

19:04.211 --> 19:05.279
ALL RIGHT.
OH. HO, HO, HO.

19:05.312 --> 19:06.580
ALL RIGHT, HOLD ON.
HOLD ON.

19:06.613 --> 19:08.415
OH.
WHOA, HO, HO, HO.

19:10.050 --> 19:12.386
YEAH, I GUESS IT'D BE NICE
TO HAVE MY GENES PASSED ON.

19:12.419 --> 19:14.488
SOMETHING OF THE IMMORTAL
IN THAT.

19:14.521 --> 19:17.191
ALL RIGHT, WHAT THE HELL?
LET'S MAKE A BABY.

19:17.224 --> 19:18.292
[ CELLPHONE RINGS ]
OKAY.

19:18.325 --> 19:19.293
ONE SECOND.

19:19.326 --> 19:20.494
ONE SECOND.

19:20.527 --> 19:22.429
ONE SECOND.
OH, GOD.

19:22.462 --> 19:23.330
YEAH. HELLO?

19:23.363 --> 19:26.500
WILL YOU PROMISE
TO NEVER LEAVE US?

19:28.435 --> 19:29.903
YES, I'LL PROMISE.

19:29.937 --> 19:33.507
OKAY, THEN.
I RELEASE YOU.

19:33.540 --> 19:35.209
FROM WHAT?

19:35.242 --> 19:38.245
FROM...WHATEVER IT IS
YOU SAY I ‐‐

19:38.278 --> 19:39.446
No, repeat.

19:39.479 --> 19:43.250
I RELEASE YOU FROM ALL HOPES
THAT WE WILL EVER BE TOGETHER.

19:43.283 --> 19:47.454
I RELEASE YOU FROM ALL HOPES
THAT WE WILL EVER BE TOGETHER.

19:47.487 --> 19:49.323
AND I ADMIT...

19:49.356 --> 19:51.825
I'VE BEEN LEADING YOU ON
SEXUALLY AND EMOTIONALLY

19:51.859 --> 19:53.160
IN ORDER
TO KEEP YOU CLOSE.

19:53.193 --> 19:55.929
OKAY, I ADMIT IT.

19:55.963 --> 19:57.865
IT'LL NEVER HAPPEN AGAIN.

19:57.898 --> 19:59.900
IT'S OVER.

19:59.933 --> 20:01.101
HAPPY?

20:01.134 --> 20:02.302
I'M NOT SURE.

20:02.336 --> 20:04.238
I THINK YOU MIGHT BE
FULL OF SHIT.

20:04.271 --> 20:07.574
THAT'S A DISTINCT POSSIBILITY.

20:07.608 --> 20:10.978
YOU'RE AN EVIL SUCCUBUS.
I'LL SEE YOU SOON.

20:11.011 --> 20:12.412
[ BEEP ]

20:12.446 --> 20:13.814
WHAT WAS ALL THAT?

20:13.847 --> 20:14.448
YOU HAVE TO GO NOW,
CRAZY CLOCK.

20:14.481 --> 20:16.049
WRONG NUMBER.

20:20.954 --> 20:23.123
THE NAKED RUN
IS AN EMPTY RITUAL.

20:23.156 --> 20:25.225
STREAKING ACROSS CAMPUS
FOR WHAT?

20:25.259 --> 20:28.595
YEAH, SO WE THOUGHT THAT
IF WE MAKE IT ABOUT SOMETHING,

20:28.629 --> 20:31.565
WE CAN PRESERVE THE RITUAL
BUT ALSO SAVE THE WORLD.

20:31.598 --> 20:34.801
SO WE'RE GONNA USE OUR BODIES
AS PROTEST SIGNS.

20:34.835 --> 20:36.003
WHAT ARE YOU PROTESTING?

20:36.036 --> 20:37.504
OFFSHORE DRILLING.

20:37.538 --> 20:38.739
AND DATE RAPE.

20:38.772 --> 20:39.740
BOTH OF THEM.
YEAH.

20:39.773 --> 20:40.741
WE COULDN'T DECIDE.

20:40.774 --> 20:43.944
DON'T DRILL OIL.

20:43.977 --> 20:45.145
OR YOUR DATE.

20:45.179 --> 20:47.447
[ Laughing ] THAT'S AWESOME!
WRITE THAT DOWN.

20:47.481 --> 20:49.483
Reporter: BUT WHAT DO YOU THINK
THE PROTEST TONIGHT

20:49.516 --> 20:51.618
IS GONNA CHANGE?

20:51.652 --> 20:52.886
YOU WOULD LIKE US

20:52.920 --> 20:55.956
TO STAY SILENT
AND COMPLACENT, WOULDN'T YOU?

20:55.989 --> 20:58.158
YEAH, SHUT UP, NEWS FATTY.

20:58.192 --> 21:00.194
IT'S JUST THE SCHOOL PAPER.
I DON'T REALLY CARE EITHER WAY.

21:00.227 --> 21:02.162
TYPICAL MEDIA BIAS.

21:02.196 --> 21:06.233
WELL, FORGIVE US FOR CARING.
GET THE HELL OUT OF HERE, MAN.

21:08.302 --> 21:09.803
WOW.

21:09.837 --> 21:12.706
YOU ARE SO PASSIONATE,
MIKE.

21:12.739 --> 21:14.541
[ BOTH CHUCKLE ]

21:15.943 --> 21:18.345
[ CELLPHONE RINGS ]

21:18.679 --> 21:21.248
OH, FUCK.

21:21.281 --> 21:22.850
ONE SEC.

21:22.883 --> 21:24.785
WHAT?

21:24.818 --> 21:26.854
WHEN?

21:26.887 --> 21:29.022
BUT I ‐‐

21:29.056 --> 21:32.759
NO!
WHAT HAPPENED TO THE VAN?

21:32.793 --> 21:35.128
NO. NO.

21:35.162 --> 21:36.563
NO!

21:38.498 --> 21:39.967
[ BEEP ]

21:40.000 --> 21:41.835
WHAT WAS THAT?

21:41.869 --> 21:43.337
[ SCOFFS ] NOTHING.

21:48.475 --> 21:50.177
KIMMI...

21:50.210 --> 21:51.712
YEAH?

21:51.745 --> 21:56.183
CAN I BORROW YOUR CAR?

21:58.485 --> 21:59.386
I HAVE BEEN SAVED.

21:59.419 --> 22:01.555
YOU SAW.
YOU HAVE TO FEED ME.

22:01.588 --> 22:04.424
YOU'RE PLAYING WITH HELLFIRE
HERE, ASSHOLES.

22:11.999 --> 22:14.701
LOOK, I'M JUST SAYING
THAT I'M CLEARLY A CHOSEN ONE,

22:14.735 --> 22:16.436
AND I THINK ‐‐
OH.

22:17.771 --> 22:19.573
A FRY.

22:26.346 --> 22:27.981
A MINIVAN.

22:28.015 --> 22:29.149
ANDY WAS REALLY GONNA DO IT,
HUH ‐‐

22:29.183 --> 22:31.952
THE KIDS, THE FAMILY,
THE WHOLE BIT?

22:31.985 --> 22:33.320
I ONCE HAD KIDS.

22:33.353 --> 22:37.758
I ONCE HAD A HOME, KIDS,
500 CD CHANGER.

22:37.791 --> 22:39.159
NOW I'M EATING FLOOR FRIES.

22:39.193 --> 22:43.463
WELL,
AT LEAST GOD WANTS ME ALIVE.

22:43.497 --> 22:44.765
THAT'S SOMETHING.

22:57.477 --> 22:58.312
[ GASPS ]

22:58.345 --> 22:59.947
SILAS!

22:59.980 --> 23:01.081
YOU GOT A CAR!

23:01.114 --> 23:03.617
YOU ARE THE HERO
OF THIS FAMILY!

23:03.650 --> 23:04.918
NO, I JUST BORROWED IT.

23:04.952 --> 23:07.888
I CAME TO SAY...GOODBYE.

23:07.921 --> 23:09.323
GOODBYE.

23:10.691 --> 23:12.192
OPEN THE TRUNK.

23:12.226 --> 23:13.594
NO!

23:13.627 --> 23:15.128
I'M STAYING.

23:15.162 --> 23:17.264
OPEN THE TRUNK.

23:17.297 --> 23:18.799
I'LL GIVE YOU A TOBLERONE.

23:18.832 --> 23:21.368
YOU SAID
THIS WAS MY DECISION.

23:21.401 --> 23:23.136
THAT WAS BEFORE.

23:23.170 --> 23:25.272
SILAS, YOU'VE ONLY KNOWN HER
FOR A COUPLE OF DAYS,

23:25.305 --> 23:28.141
AND THIS IS CRISIS TIME HERE,
SO OPEN THE FUCKING TRUNK.

23:34.948 --> 23:37.050
SWEETIE.

23:38.452 --> 23:40.354
SWEETIE.

23:49.897 --> 23:51.365
[ TRUNK CLOSES ]

23:51.398 --> 23:56.303
I WANT YOU TO PULL AROUND
TO THE ROOM SO WE CAN PACK.

23:58.572 --> 24:00.140
AND I'M ‐‐ I'M SORRY.

24:00.174 --> 24:03.310
I BET SHE WAS
COMPLETELY ADORABLE.

24:04.444 --> 24:06.146
FUCK.

24:07.981 --> 24:11.018
[ MUFFLED GRUNTING, THUMPING ]

24:18.225 --> 24:20.460
WHAT THE FUCK
ARE YOU DOING HERE?

24:20.494 --> 24:23.397
[ MUFFLED GRUNTING ]

24:25.365 --> 24:28.035
MM‐HMM. MM‐HMM.
MM‐HMM. MM‐HMM.

24:31.972 --> 24:34.408
KIMMI:
Hey, how's my car?

24:34.441 --> 24:36.043
YEAH, IT'S CUTE.

24:36.076 --> 24:38.478
I LIKE THE DREAM CATCHER.

24:38.512 --> 24:42.049
[ MUFFLED GRUNTING ]
[ Chuckles ]
It caught me you.

24:42.082 --> 24:44.418
So, I'll see you tonight?

24:44.451 --> 24:46.119
I'LL BE THERE.

24:46.153 --> 24:47.821
[ ALARM CHIRPS ]

24:47.855 --> 24:48.822
[ MUFFLED GRUNTING ]

24:48.856 --> 24:51.892
SO...WHAT HAPPENED
AFTER I LEFT?

24:51.925 --> 24:52.893
ANDY!

24:52.926 --> 24:54.595
[ STEVIE FUSSES ]

24:54.628 --> 24:57.097
WE GOT TO GO, NOW!

24:57.130 --> 24:59.600
CAN'T HELP
BUT BE IMPRESSED, HUH?

24:59.633 --> 25:00.801
WHOA.
WERE YOU IN A FIGHT?

25:00.834 --> 25:02.069
WHERE'S SHANE?

25:02.102 --> 25:04.371
I SENT HIM TO THE VENDING
MACHINE FOR FLEEING SNACKS.

25:04.404 --> 25:05.472
UH, OUT NOW.

25:05.506 --> 25:07.741
DRY. GO.
BRING STEVIE.

25:16.850 --> 25:19.253
SHIT!

25:19.286 --> 25:21.121
SHIT.

25:21.154 --> 25:22.489
SHAWN: This is Shawn.

25:22.523 --> 25:24.258
You must be old
if you're not texting.

25:24.291 --> 25:26.627
So leave a message, mom.
[ Beep ]

25:26.660 --> 25:30.497
SHANE, WHEREVER YOU ARE,
HIDE!

25:30.531 --> 25:33.000
[ Dialing ]

25:33.033 --> 25:34.868
[ Ringing ]
ANDY, STAY IN HERE WITH STEVIE!

25:34.902 --> 25:36.003
DON'T COME OUT!

25:36.036 --> 25:37.771
SILAS: Leave a message.

25:37.804 --> 25:40.107
[ Beep ]
SHIT!

25:40.140 --> 25:42.176
SILAS, DRIVE AWAY.

25:42.209 --> 25:43.310
DANGER.

25:43.343 --> 25:45.145
Danger, danger.

25:46.947 --> 25:47.915
DANGER.

25:47.948 --> 25:49.316
UM...

25:49.349 --> 25:52.419
Danger. Danger.

25:58.692 --> 26:00.460
AAH! [ GRUNTS ]

26:01.895 --> 26:03.130
[ DOOR SLAMS ]

26:03.163 --> 26:05.132
NOW THIS
IS JUST DEPRESSING.

26:05.165 --> 26:07.201
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]
THERE'S A VERY DANGEROUS MAN.

26:07.234 --> 26:09.469
YOU RIPPED MY EAR.
NOW I CAN'T WEAR EARRINGS.

26:09.503 --> 26:12.206
WHEN YOU AIN'T GOT NO HAIR,
THAT'S YOUR FLAIR!

